30/11/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Authorities detained 18 former government and other officials late Wednesday (November 29th), in a large-scale operation against corruption and organised crime.
Media reports suggest the detainees include three former deputy ministers, though no names were released.
They and others reportedly face charges of abuse of office, money laundering and corruption stemming from different affairs worth millions of euros.
(A1 TV, Makfax - 30/11/06)
